1
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,928
ARCHER: STARFLEET
DIDN'T SEND US OUT HERE

2
00:00:10,970 --> 00:00:14,055
TO HUMILIATE OURSELVES.

3
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:17,893
HOW LONG WERE WE IN ORBIT,
GROVELING?

4
00:00:17,935 --> 00:00:19,520
SIX DAYS?

5
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:22,063
HOSHI: FIVE, SIR, AND IT
WASN'T EXACTLY GROVELING.

6
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:24,692
APOLOGIZING...
ASKING FORGIVENESS...

7
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,025
JUST BECAUSE WE ATE LUNCH

8
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:28,570
IN FRONT OF THEM
ON OUR OWN SHIP, MONTHS AGO.

9
00:00:28,612 --> 00:00:29,780
I CALL THAT GROVELING.

10
00:00:29,822 --> 00:00:31,281
HOSHI: THEY WERE OFFENDED.

11
00:00:31,323 --> 00:00:33,534
T'POL: THE KREETASSANS
MANUFACTURE PLASMA INJECTORS.

12
00:00:33,575 --> 00:00:34,576
WE NEED ONE.

13
00:00:34,618 --> 00:00:37,078
SO WE SPEND SIX DAYS
GROVELING...

14
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:38,622
FIVE DAYS.

15
00:00:38,664 --> 00:00:41,000
AND WHEN THEY FINALLY
AGREE TO TALK TO US,

16
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,835
WE GO DOWN, AND WHAT DO THEY DO?

17
00:00:42,877 --> 00:00:46,672
THEY KEEP US WAITING
FOR 12 HOURS

18
00:00:46,714 --> 00:00:47,840
AND THEN SEND US PACKING.

19
00:00:47,882 --> 00:00:50,676
NO EXPLANATION,
NO PLASMA INJECTOR.

20
00:00:50,718 --> 00:00:52,803
JUST "LEAVE.
GO BACK TO YOUR SHIP!"

21
00:00:52,845 --> 00:00:55,806
T'POL: WE OBVIOUSLY
OFFENDED THEM AGAIN.

22
00:00:55,848 --> 00:00:58,225
ARCHER: MAYBE MY HAIR'S
PARTED ON THE WRONG SIDE.

23
00:00:58,266 --> 00:01:01,186
I'M EXHAUSTED AND I'VE HAD IT
WITH THESE PEOPLE.

24
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,938
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

25
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:04,690
GO AHEAD.

26
00:01:04,732 --> 00:01:06,650
Phlox: The three of you
are clear to go,

27
00:01:06,692 --> 00:01:08,944
but I'm afraid I'll need
to keep Porthos for a while.

28
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:10,863
ARCHER: WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

29
00:01:10,905 --> 00:01:13,824
Phlox: He picked up a pathogen
of some kind on the surface.

30
00:01:13,866 --> 00:01:15,910
Neither decon agent
has been effective.

31
00:01:15,951 --> 00:01:17,160
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?

32
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,704
Phlox: I'm not sure yet.

33
00:01:18,746 --> 00:01:20,998
I'll let you know as soon
as I've run some tests.

34
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:26,127
FEEL BETTER, PORTHOS.

35
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:29,088
DOC'LL HAVE YOU GOOD AS NEW
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

36
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:32,551
I MIGHT EVEN BREAK
THE NO-CHEESE RULE TONIGHT.

37
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,764
[ BARKS ]

38
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,181
SORRY, FELLA.

39
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:39,934
YOU GOT TO STAY.

40
00:01:53,072 --> 00:01:57,659
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

41
00:01:57,701 --> 00:02:00,913
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

42
00:02:00,955 --> 00:02:04,875
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

43
00:02:04,917 --> 00:02:08,503
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

44
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:12,883
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

45
00:02:12,925 --> 00:02:16,553
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

46
00:02:16,595 --> 00:02:20,515
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

47
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,435
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

48
00:02:23,477 --> 00:02:26,897
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

49
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:28,315
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

50
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:31,944
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

51
00:02:31,986 --> 00:02:36,907
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

52
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:39,493
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

53
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:44,039
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

54
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:47,167
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

55
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:52,923
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

56
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:54,508
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

57
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:56,885
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

58
00:02:56,927 --> 00:03:00,597
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

59
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:05,226
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

60
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:23,202
TRIP: WE'RE PLAYING
WITH FIRE, CAPTAIN.

61
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:24,663
IT'S JUST A MATTER OF TIME

62
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,665
BEFORE THIS INJECTOR
GIVES UP THE GHOST.

63
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:28,500
ARCHER: YOU'VE GOT FOUR MORE.

64
00:03:28,542 --> 00:03:29,793
THE SHIP CAN RUN ON FOUR.

65
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:32,546
YEAH, BUT IT CAN'T
RUN ON THREE.

66
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,506
YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
AT WARP SPEED

67
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:37,092
WHEN YOU'VE ONLY GOT THREE
PLASMA INJECTORS ONLINE.

68
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:39,053
ARCHER: WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF US LOSING ANOTHER ONE

69
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,929
BEFORE WE FIND A REPLACEMENT?

70
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:43,140
I'M NOT COMFORTABLE
WITH FOUR, CAPTAIN.

71
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:46,267
WE<i> NEED</i> FIVE.

72
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:48,603
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
DOWN THERE, ANYWAY?

73
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,565
T'POL THINKS
WE INSULTED THEM AGAIN.

74
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,859
HOW?

75
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:56,070
YOU DIDN'T EAT CABBAGE
BEFORE YOU LEFT.

76
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:57,863
I WAS A PERFECT GENTLEMAN.

77
00:03:57,905 --> 00:04:00,074
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO GO SOMEWHERE ELSE

78
00:04:00,115 --> 00:04:01,449
TO FIND YOU YOUR INJECTOR, TRIP.

79
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:02,910
THESE PEOPLE ARE IMPOSSIBLE.

80
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:05,204
THEIR COMPONENTS ARE
METALLURGICALLY SOUND,

81
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:06,287
DEPENDABLE...

82
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,331
WE COULD LOOK FOR SIX MONTHS

83
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:11,752
AND NOT FIND ANYTHING
HALF AS COMPATIBLE.

84
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:14,004
YOU'RE A TRAINED DIPLOMAT --

85
00:04:14,046 --> 00:04:15,923
TAKE THE HIGH ROAD.

86
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:18,926
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOME WAY
YOU CAN KISS AND MAKE UP.

87
00:04:21,053 --> 00:04:22,763
I'LL HAVE T'POL SEE

88
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:26,183
IF SHE CAN FIND OUT WHAT WE DID.

89
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:30,270
BUT I'M NOT PROMISING ANYTHING.

90
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:31,688
I WENT TO DECON.

91
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:33,481
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
DOWN THERE WITH PORTHOS.

92
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:34,608
IS EV--

93
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,193
PHLOX: IT'S ALL RIGHT
TO PET HIM.

94
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:39,238
YOU'LL HAVE TO USE
THE ISOLATION GLOVES.

95
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,448
ARCHER: DID YOU RUN YOUR TESTS?

96
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:44,743
PHLOX: HIS AUTOIMMUNE SYSTEM
IS COLLAPSING.

97
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:46,078
I'VE ISOLATED THE PATHOGEN,

98
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,328
BROKEN DOWN
ITS PROTEIN SEQUENCE.

99
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,663
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT, CAPTAIN.

100
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:50,999
IT SHOULDN'T BE
AFFECTING HIM LIKE THIS,

101
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:53,085
BUT IT IS.

102
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,297
ARCHER:
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

103
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:59,133
PHLOX: RUNNING MORE TESTS.

104
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:01,176
I'M SURE I'LL COME UP
WITH SOMETHING.

105
00:05:01,218 --> 00:05:03,262
HOW SURE?

106
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:06,932
COULD...THIS BE
LIFE-THREATENING?

107
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:08,767
IT'S TOO EARLY TO TELL.

108
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:18,318
DIDN'T WE SEND HIS GENOME TO
THE KREETASSANS ALONG WITH OURS?

109
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:19,611
I TRANSMITTED THEM MYSELF

110
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,196
BEFORE YOU LEFT<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

111
00:05:21,238 --> 00:05:23,240
SO SHOULDN'T THEY HAVE NOTICED
THERE'S A PATHOGEN

112
00:05:23,282 --> 00:05:25,826
IN THEIR ATMOSPHERE THAT
HIS IMMUNE SYSTEM CAN'T HANDLE?

113
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:26,994
THEY SHOULD HAVE...

114
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:29,621
ASSUMING THEY TOOK
THE TIME TO CHECK.

115
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:35,376
I'M TOLD I'VE OFFENDED
THESE PEOPLE TWICE.

116
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:37,254
ONCE FOR EATING
IN FRONT OF THEM.

117
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:40,966
THE SECOND TIME,
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT FOR.

118
00:05:41,008 --> 00:05:43,468
BUT IF THEIR CARELESSNESS
HAS HURT PORTHOS,

119
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,511
OR GOD FORBID,

120
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:48,265
ENDS UP KILLING HIM...

121
00:05:48,307 --> 00:05:51,143
THEY'RE GOING TO FIND OUT WHAT
BEING OFFENDED IS ALL ABOUT.

122
00:05:51,185 --> 00:05:54,604
PORTHOS HAS NO INTENTION
OF GIVING UP...

123
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:56,273
AND NEITHER DO I.

124
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:08,827
YOU HEAR THAT, BOY?

125
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:13,332
HMM?

126
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:15,250
WE'RE ALL PULLING FOR YOU.

127
00:06:20,421 --> 00:06:21,422
DID YOU REACH THEM?

128
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:23,008
T'POL: YES.

129
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,759
AND?

130
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:28,429
I THINK WE SHOULD DISCUSS THIS
IN YOUR READY ROOM.

131
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:36,688
WELL?

132
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,274
DO YOU RECALL THE STAND OF TREES
OUTSIDE THE HALL OF DIPLOMACY?

133
00:06:39,316 --> 00:06:40,901
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

134
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:43,362
THEY'RE ALVERA TREES...
OVER 300 YEARS OLD.

135
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:44,988
THAT'S FASCINATING.

136
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,406
DID YOU APOLOGIZE
FOR WHATEVER WE DID WRONG?

137
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,910
ARE WE GOING TO GET
OUR PLASMA INJECTOR?

138
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:51,619
THE KREETASSANS CONSIDER

139
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:54,331
THE ALVERA TREES
CULTURAL TREASURES.

140
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:57,000
APPARENTLY PORTHOS
URINATED ON ONE OF THEM.

141
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:58,710
AND THAT'S WHAT
THEY'RE INSULTED ABOUT?

142
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:00,254
IT<i> IS</i> UNDERSTANDABLE.

143
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:01,880
WELL, MAYBE IF THEY'D
HAVE BOTHERED

144
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,340
TO READ THE GENETIC
PROFILE WE SENT,

145
00:07:03,382 --> 00:07:05,717
THEY'D HAVE TOLD US
TO LEAVE THE DOG ON THE SHIP

146
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:07,261
AND THEN HE WOULDN'T
HAVE HAD AN OPPORTUNITY

147
00:07:07,302 --> 00:07:10,055
TO PEE ON ONE
OF THEIR PRECIOUS TREES.

148
00:07:10,097 --> 00:07:11,723
I CONVEYED
YOUR SINCEREST APOLOGIES

149
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,267
TO THE CHANCELLERY.

150
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:14,684
THEY'RE DISCUSSING
POSSIBLE ACTS OF CONTRITION.

151
00:07:14,726 --> 00:07:16,019
WHERE THE HELL DO YOU GET OFF

152
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:18,230
CONVEYING<i> MY</i> SINCEREST
APOLOGIES?

153
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:20,107
THEY'RE THE ONES
WHO SHOULD BE SORRY.

154
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,441
I DON'T NEED TO REMIND YOU

155
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:23,110
THAT COMMANDER TUCKER
IS RELYING ON US.

156
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:24,485
THERE ARE SOME THINGS

157
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:27,948
MORE IMPORTANT
THAN PLASMA INJECTORS.

158
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:31,659
ARE YOU REFERRING TO YOUR PRIDE?

159
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:34,204
I'LL TELL YOU ONE THING,
SUBCOMMANDER...

160
00:07:34,246 --> 00:07:36,831
IF ANYTHING HAPPENS TO PORTHOS,

161
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:41,086
I'LL BE THE ONE
WATERING THEIR ALVERA TREES.

162
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:52,097
[ BALL BOUNCES OFF WALL ]

163
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,418
PHLOX: IF YOU WERE
A MARRIED MAN,

164
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:24,504
I'D BE WONDERING IF YOUR
WIFE HAD THROWN YOU OUT.

165
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,756
I JUST THOUGHT
IT MIGHT CHEER PORTHOS UP

166
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,591
IF I SLEPT HERE TONIGHT.

167
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,427
THAT IS,
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT WITH YOU.

168
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,929
I DON'T THINK YOUR DOG
IS IN ANY CONDITION TO KNOW

169
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:34,222
WHETHER YOU'RE HERE OR NOT.

170
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:37,642
WELL, THEN,
MAYBE IT'LL CHEER ME UP.

171
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:42,772
BE MY GUEST.
TAKE YOUR PICK.

172
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:43,940
HOW'S PORTHOS DOING?

173
00:08:43,982 --> 00:08:45,275
PHLOX: MY SUB-MAMMALIAN DATABASE

174
00:08:45,317 --> 00:08:47,902
CONTAINS NO PERTINENT FILES
ON "BUGLES,"

175
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,904
BUT, UM, THERE'S
SUFFICIENT INFORMATION

176
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:51,531
ON SIMILAR CHORDATA.

177
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:53,116
"BEAGLES."

178
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:54,951
YES.

179
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:57,537
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION, DOC,

180
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:59,498
JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY.

181
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:03,251
ARE THERE ANY DOGS
ON YOUR HOMEWORLD?

182
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,422
THE DENOBULAN LEMUR
IS HIGHLY SOUGHT AFTER.

183
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:10,591
IT'S NOT EXACTLY A DOG,
BUT YOU COULD SAY IT'S DOGLIKE.

184
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:14,929
IT HAS A TAIL, FUR...
MOST HAVE ONE HEAD.

185
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:18,599
DID YOUR MEDICAL TRAINING
INCLUDE ANY...

186
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,018
PHLOX: CAPTAIN, PLEASE.

187
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,269
YOU NEEDN'T BE CONCERNED.

188
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:22,396
I HOLD SIX DEGREES

189
00:09:22,437 --> 00:09:24,523
IN INTERSPECIES
VETERINARY MEDICINE.

190
00:09:24,605 --> 00:09:28,443
I THOUGHT YOU WERE JUST,
YOU KNOW...A PEOPLE DOCTOR.

191
00:09:28,485 --> 00:09:29,944
AS A MATTER OF FACT,

192
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:32,072
I'VE ALSO EARNED DEGREES
IN DENTISTRY, HEMATOLOGY,

193
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,532
BOTANICAL PHARMACOLOGY...

194
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,616
I'M IMPRESSED.

195
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:40,663
SO, HOW'S HE DOING?

196
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,790
I BELIEVE I'VE ELIMINATED
THE PATHOGEN.

197
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:44,334
THE QUESTION IS

198
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:45,752
WHETHER THE TREATMENT
I'VE DEVISED

199
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:51,508
WILL STABILIZE
HIS AUTOIMMUNE SYSTEM BEFORE...

200
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:54,428
BEFORE WHAT?

201
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:56,596
IN A FEW HOURS, I'LL HAVE
A MORE DETAILED PROGNOSIS.

202
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:59,099
BEFORE WHAT, DOCTOR?

203
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:04,104
THERE ARE MANY HARMLESS STRAINS
OF BACTERIA

204
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:05,272
THAT CAN BECOME LETHAL

205
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:07,023
WHEN THE IMMUNE SYSTEM
IS COMPROMISED.

206
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:10,527
BUT IT IS TOO EARLY
TO BE THINKING ABOUT THAT.

207
00:10:10,569 --> 00:10:12,070
HMM?

208
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:15,449
NOW, WE SHOULD BOTH TRY
TO GET A FEW HOURS OF REST.

209
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:17,617
IF THERE ARE ANY CHANGES
IN HIS VITAL SIGNS,

210
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:20,537
THE ALARMS ARE QUITE LOUD.

211
00:10:20,579 --> 00:10:22,705
GOOD NIGHT.

212
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,214
I WOULD HAVE BROUGHT YOU
SOME CHEESE,

213
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:35,718
BUT DR. PHLOX WOULDN'T
HAVE LET ME GIVE YOU ANY.

214
00:10:44,561 --> 00:10:46,480
[ SIGHS ]

215
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:12,589
[ ELECTRICAL BUZZING ]

216
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:26,394
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

217
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:35,778
[ SAW BUZZING ]

218
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:42,452
DOCTOR, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

219
00:11:42,494 --> 00:11:44,912
I'M SORRY, CAPTAIN.
DID I WAKE YOU?

220
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:47,582
JUST TRIMMING MY TOENAILS.

221
00:11:47,624 --> 00:11:48,958
THEY GROW QUITE RAPIDLY.

222
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,294
HAVE TO KEEP THEM GROOMED
AT LEAST ONCE A WEEK.

223
00:11:51,336 --> 00:11:54,797
JUST WANTED TO BE SURE
YOU'RE OKAY.

224
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:56,216
THANKS FOR YOUR CONCERN.

225
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:57,551
GOOD NIGHT.

226
00:12:14,901 --> 00:12:17,820
[ SQUEAKING, CAGE RATTLING ]

227
00:12:24,077 --> 00:12:26,329
[ SCRAPING ]

228
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:34,713
[ SCRAPING CONTINUES ]

229
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:40,759
[ CHIRPING ]

230
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:42,761
[ LOUD CHIRP ]

231
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:45,724
[ RUSTLING, CHIRPING ]

232
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:47,726
I'M SORRY, CAPTAIN.

233
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:49,728
DID I WAKE YOU AGAIN?

234
00:12:49,768 --> 00:12:51,312
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

235
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:54,107
FEEDING TIME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

236
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,109
DON'T BE GREEDY!

237
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:58,777
HOW LONG WAS I ASLEEP?

238
00:12:58,819 --> 00:13:01,072
NEARLY AN HOUR.

239
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:03,617
DOES THIS GO ON EVERY NIGHT?

240
00:13:03,658 --> 00:13:05,619
ONLY WHEN I'M HERE.

241
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:08,787
THEY'RE VERY DEMANDING
WHEN THEY KNOW I'M IN SICK BAY.

242
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:12,417
GREAT.

243
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:13,752
PORTHOS?

244
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:16,546
I'LL STILL NEED
AT LEAST A COUPLE OF HOURS.

245
00:13:16,588 --> 00:13:17,756
IS HE COMFORTABLE?

246
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:19,758
HE'S FAST ASLEEP.

247
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:22,176
I'M GLAD TO SEE SOMEONE IS.

248
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:27,432
I'LL CHECK BACK
IN A COUPLE HOURS.

249
00:14:11,309 --> 00:14:12,893
HOW'S YOUR DOG?

250
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:15,104
ARCHER: NICE OF YOU TO ASK.

251
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:17,732
WE'LL KNOW IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.

252
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:22,069
[ BEEPS ]

253
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:25,865
[ TREADMILL WHIRS FASTER ]

254
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:28,493
[ BEEPS ]

255
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:30,787
[ TREADMILL WHIRS FASTER ]

256
00:14:30,829 --> 00:14:33,498
HAVE YOU HEARD FROM YOUR FRIENDS
ON THE SURFACE?

257
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:34,833
NOT YET.

258
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,501
I GUESS THEY HAVEN'T FINISHED

259
00:14:36,543 --> 00:14:38,795
COMPILING THEIR LIST
OF PUNISHMENTS.

260
00:14:38,837 --> 00:14:41,589
THEY'RE NOT INTERESTED
IN PUNISHING YOU.

261
00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:44,217
THEY ONLY WANT
AN APPROPRIATE APOLOGY.

262
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:46,886
I'M SORRY!

263
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,847
FOR WHAT?

264
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,473
JUST PRACTICING.

265
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,477
[ BEEPS ]

266
00:14:54,519 --> 00:14:57,564
[ TREADMILL WHIRS FASTER ]

267
00:14:57,605 --> 00:14:59,399
[ BEEPS ]

268
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,692
[ TREADMILL WHIRS FASTER ]

269
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:02,151
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE BROUGHT
YOUR DOG

270
00:15:02,193 --> 00:15:04,237
ON A DIPLOMATIC MISSION,
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING

271
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,113
WE HAD PREVIOUSLY
OFFENDED THE KREETASSANS.

272
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:08,533
THEY KNEW WE WERE BRINGING HIM.

273
00:15:08,575 --> 00:15:11,369
WE EVEN SENT HIS GENETIC SPECS.

274
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:14,748
THEY COULD HAVE ASKED US
TO LEAVE HIM BEHIND.

275
00:15:14,789 --> 00:15:16,541
THEY DIDN'T!

276
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:20,127
[ Breathlessly ] PORTHOS HAS
THE RIGHT TO A LITTLE FRESH AIR.

277
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:22,881
T'POL: YOU'RE ONCE
AGAIN IGNORING

278
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,465
THE CONSEQUENCES
OF YOUR ACTIONS.

279
00:15:24,507 --> 00:15:26,342
ARCHER: WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

280
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:28,177
YOU OBVIOUSLY PLACE
MORE IMPORTANCE

281
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:30,179
ON THE QUALITY
OF THE AIR YOUR PET BREATHES

282
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:31,806
THAN ON THE QUALITY
OF THE PLASMA

283
00:15:31,848 --> 00:15:33,558
THAT DRIVES YOUR SHIP.

284
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:36,394
ARCHER: WHAT THE HELL DOES ONE
HAVE TO DO WITH THE OTHER?

285
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:38,396
ISN'T IT LOGICAL...

286
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:41,566
I COULD...CARE
ABOUT MY SHIP<i> AND</i> MY DOG?

287
00:15:41,608 --> 00:15:44,110
T'POL: I'M NOT QUESTIONING
YOUR PLURALITIES.

288
00:15:44,151 --> 00:15:47,530
I'M QUESTIONING YOUR<i> PRIORITIES.</i>

289
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,450
ARCHER: I REALLY THOUGHT

290
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:53,119
YOU WERE BEGINNING
TO UNDERSTAND SOMETHING

291
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,621
ABOUT HUMAN FEELINGS.

292
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:57,039
T'POL: NOT WHEN IT PERTAINS
TO PRIMITIVE QUADRUPEDS

293
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:59,292
WHO HAVEN'T DEVELOPED
THE ABILITY TO SPEAK

294
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,960
OR TO USE A TOILET.

295
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:02,253
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]

296
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:04,255
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

297
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:08,008
I OBVIOUSLY CAN'T
KEEP UP WITH YOU.

298
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,260
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

299
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:10,804
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

300
00:16:10,845 --> 00:16:12,221
T'POL.

301
00:16:12,263 --> 00:16:13,848
Hoshi: We've just received
a transmission

302
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,391
from the Kreetassans.

303
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:17,184
IT'S THEIR
RECONCILIATION DEMANDS.

304
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:18,770
THE CAPTAIN'S NOT GOING
TO BELIEVE THIS.

305
00:16:18,812 --> 00:16:20,647
ARCHER: YOU'D BE
SURPRISED, HOSHI.

306
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:21,898
CAPTAIN, I DIDN'T --

307
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,023
ARCHER: IT'S
ALL RIGHT, ENSIGN.

308
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:26,277
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

309
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:45,964
[ CHUCKLES ]

310
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:48,800
WELL, THIS ISN'T SO BAD.

311
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:50,593
I WAS SURE THERE'D BE
SOMETHING IN HERE

312
00:16:50,635 --> 00:16:52,512
ABOUT STANDING ON ONE FOOT
WITH MY EYES SHUT

313
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:56,265
RECITING "THE NIGHT
BEFORE CHRISTMAS."

314
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:57,809
I'M GOING BACK TO SICK BAY --

315
00:16:57,851 --> 00:16:59,226
SEE IF I CAN GET AN HOUR'S SLEEP

316
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,896
BEFORE THE DOCTOR'S
RESULTS COME THROUGH.

317
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:03,439
LET ME KNOW IF THIS FITS

318
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:07,318
WITH YOUR DEFINITION
OF AN APPROPRIATE APOLOGY.

319
00:17:09,863 --> 00:17:13,032
[ SIGHS ]

320
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:16,410
DO WE HAVE A CHAIN SAW ONBOARD?

321
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:25,003
[ ALARM BLARING ]

322
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:29,048
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

323
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:32,552
PHLOX: HE'S GONE
INTO ANAPHYLACTIC SHOCK.

324
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:35,805
HIS BODY'S REJECTING
THE TREATMENT I SELECTED.

325
00:17:35,847 --> 00:17:38,892
YOU SAID WE'D KNOW IN A FEW
HOURS IF THIS WOULD WORK.

326
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,351
PHLOX: EXACTLY.

327
00:17:40,393 --> 00:17:42,144
IT'S NOT WORKING.

328
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,147
IS HE GOING TO DIE?

329
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:47,483
FILL THIS WITH 5 cc's
OF TETRASOL.

330
00:17:47,525 --> 00:17:51,779
IT'S THE BLUE FLUID,
SECOND ON THE RIGHT -- 5 cc's.

331
00:17:57,035 --> 00:17:59,579
5 cc's.

332
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:14,886
I DON'T THINK SO.

333
00:18:14,928 --> 00:18:16,220
WHAT?

334
00:18:16,262 --> 00:18:19,181
YOU ASKED ME IF HE
WAS GOING TO DIE.

335
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:22,727
[ SIGHS ]

336
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:26,230
ARE YOU TRYING
A DIFFERENT TREATMENT?

337
00:18:26,272 --> 00:18:28,066
MM-HMM.

338
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:30,068
LET ME GUESS -- WE'LL KNOW IN...

339
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:32,194
PHLOX:
A COUPLE OF HOURS, YES.

340
00:18:35,907 --> 00:18:38,451
HOW ARE THINGS PROGRESSING
WITH THE KREETASSANS?

341
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:41,370
THEY'VE GOT A PERFECTLY GOOD
PLASMA INJECTOR

342
00:18:41,412 --> 00:18:43,372
SITTING ON A SHELF SOMEWHERE.

343
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:47,126
BUT WILL THEY SHARE IT WITH US?

344
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,544
[ CHUCKLES ]

345
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:50,588
NOT UNTIL I MAKE A FOOL
OF MYSELF

346
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:54,842
BY GOING THROUGH SOME SERIES
OF RITUAL APOLOGIES.

347
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:57,804
THE FACT THAT PORTHOS
IS ON DEATH'S DOORSTEP

348
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,931
DOESN'T SEEM TO BOTHER
ANY OF THEM.

349
00:18:59,973 --> 00:19:03,935
THEY'RE THE ONES WHO SHOULD BE
APOLOGIZING, NOT ME!

350
00:19:03,977 --> 00:19:08,022
T'POL THINKS I CARE MORE
ABOUT MY DOG THAN MY SHIP!

351
00:19:08,064 --> 00:19:10,900
ISN'T<i> THAT</i> DELIGHTFUL?

352
00:19:10,942 --> 00:19:12,819
WHY DOES T'POL'S OPINION
CONCERN YOU?

353
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,279
SHE'S MY SCIENCE OFFICER,
MY SECOND-IN-COMMAND.

354
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:17,406
SHE SHOULD KNOW,
MORE THAN ANYONE ABOARD,

355
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:19,366
HOW DEDICATED I AM
TO THIS MISSION --

356
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:21,327
TO EVERY MEMBER OF MY CREW.

357
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:23,454
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER MY QUESTION.

358
00:19:23,496 --> 00:19:25,456
PORTHOS HAS ONE PAW
IN BEAGLE HEAVEN

359
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:28,167
BECAUSE THESE JERKS
DIDN'T BOTHER TO LOOK

360
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,209
AT HIS GENETIC PROFILE.

361
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:30,544
AM I SUPPOSED TO IGNORE THAT?

362
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:32,005
I WOULD THINK YOU'D BE
MORE INTERESTED

363
00:19:32,046 --> 00:19:34,007
IN COMMANDER TUCKER'S OPINION.

364
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,134
YOU'VE KNOWN HIM FOR MANY YEARS,
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN.

365
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:39,137
IT WOULD BE NICE TO HAVE ALL
FIVE PLASMA INJECTORS WORKING,

366
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:41,639
BUT IT'S NOT ESSENTIAL.

367
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:43,182
WE CAN DO FINE WITH FOUR.

368
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:46,144
AND THE FIFTH ONE JUST STARTED
TO ACT UP.

369
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:48,938
WE MIGHT GET ANOTHER
10 LIGHT-YEARS OUT OF IT.

370
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:50,815
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED
THAT YOUR ANGER

371
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:52,817
MAY ENCOMPASS MORE
THAN JUST PORTHOS

372
00:19:52,859 --> 00:19:55,028
PHLOX: AND THE KREETASSANS?
ARCHER: WHAT?

373
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:56,320
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN

374
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:57,780
SINCE YOU WERE INTIMATE
WITH A WOMAN?

375
00:19:57,822 --> 00:19:59,198
ARCHER: WHAT?!

376
00:19:59,239 --> 00:20:01,617
PHLOX: HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN --
ARCHER: I HEARD YOU!

377
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:03,036
I SUPPOSE
YOU'RE GOING TO TELL ME

378
00:20:03,077 --> 00:20:05,204
YOU HAVE A DEGREE
IN PSYCHIATRY, TOO.

379
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:07,123
ABSOLUTELY.

380
00:20:07,165 --> 00:20:09,125
UNH-UNH.

381
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:11,585
NO WAY. NOT A CHANCE.

382
00:20:11,627 --> 00:20:14,380
PORTHOS IS THE ONLY PATIENT
YOU'RE TREATING RIGHT NOW.

383
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:15,589
YOU GOT THAT?

384
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:18,176
LET ME KNOW
IF THERE'S ANY CHANGE.

385
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:33,607
[ SIGHS ]

386
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:42,241
<i>WHY HAVEN'T YOU ADJUSTED</i>
<i>YOUR TIME TO OUR CAPITAL CITY?</i>

387
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:43,659
HOSHI: I APOLOGIZE.

388
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,161
WE WEREN'T AWARE
THAT IT WAS REQUIRED.

389
00:20:45,203 --> 00:20:46,662
KREETASSAN:
<i>IT ISN'T A</i> REQUIREMENT.

390
00:20:46,704 --> 00:20:48,789
<i>IT IS SIMPLY A COURTESY --</i>

391
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:52,501
<i>SOMETHING YOUR SPECIES</i>
<i>DOESN'T SEEM TO UNDERSTAND.</i>

392
00:20:52,543 --> 00:20:54,420
I'LL EXPLAIN IT
TO THE CAPTAIN IMMEDIATELY.

393
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:57,715
KREETASSAN:<i> YOU MIGHT ALSO</i>
<i>EXPLAIN TO YOUR CAPTAIN</i>

394
00:20:57,757 --> 00:20:59,633
<i>THAT IT'S BEEN</i>
<i>NEARLY THREE HOURS</i>

395
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:01,677
<i>SINCE HE RECEIVED</i>
<i>OUR TRANSMISSION.</i>

396
00:21:01,719 --> 00:21:03,637
<i>IF HE HAS THE SLIGHTEST HOPE</i>

397
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:07,100
<i>OF ACQUIRING ANY TECHNOLOGY</i>
<i>FROM US, HE'D BE WISE</i>

398
00:21:07,141 --> 00:21:08,809
<i>TO PAY US THE COURTESY</i>

399
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:11,062
KREETASSAN:<i> OF RESPONDING.</i> 
HOSHI: I UNDERSTAND. I'LL --

400
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:14,356
I'LL LET HIM KNOW.

401
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:19,361
[ PHLOX SPEAKING DENOBULAN ]

402
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:23,282
[ SQUEAKING ]

403
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:26,994
KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN!

404
00:21:27,036 --> 00:21:28,204
OHH!

405
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:30,289
NO MATTER WHAT I DO
TO SECURE HER CAGE,

406
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,875
SHE ALWAYS FINDS A WAY
TO GET OUT.

407
00:21:34,585 --> 00:21:36,921
[ SIGHS ]

408
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:58,109
[ SQUEAKING ]

409
00:22:21,215 --> 00:22:23,092
[ HOOTING ]

410
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:30,474
[ SQUEAKING ]

411
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:34,145
[ GRUNTING ]

412
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:35,938
[ GRUNTS ]

413
00:22:44,155 --> 00:22:45,447
OH!

414
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:50,119
I THOUGHT YOU SAID YOUR BAT

415
00:22:50,161 --> 00:22:52,370
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE TERRIFIED
OF THAT THING.

416
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:53,580
IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN.

417
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:56,374
PYRITHIAN MOON HAWKS
EAT THESE BATS.

418
00:22:56,416 --> 00:22:58,376
[ GROANS ]

419
00:22:58,418 --> 00:23:00,546
OH, I KNOW
I GOT THE SILHOUETTE RIGHT.

420
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:05,301
AND I MASTERED THE CALL...
YEARS AGO.

421
00:23:05,343 --> 00:23:07,053
[ COOS SOFTLY ]

422
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:08,428
[ GROANS ]

423
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:11,098
ARCHER: THAT STUFF ISN'T
POISONOUS, IS IT?

424
00:23:13,391 --> 00:23:15,393
NAH, I'LL BE FINE.

425
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:17,395
ARCHER: WHAT NOW?

426
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:21,359
WE NEED TO FIND HER
BEFORE WE CAN CATCH HER.

427
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:23,610
SHE'LL STAY UP HIGH.

428
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:44,757
HAVE YOU THOUGHT ANY MORE
ABOUT WHY T'POL'S OPINION

429
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:46,466
IS SO IMPORTANT TO YOU?

430
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:51,097
IT'S 2:30 IN THE MORNING,
AND I'M HUNTING AN ESCAPED BAT.

431
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:53,933
THAT'S ALL I'M THINKING ABOUT
RIGHT NOW, DOCTOR.

432
00:23:53,974 --> 00:23:55,684
THAT AND PORTHOS.

433
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:57,395
PHLOX: SEXUAL TENSION, CAPTAIN.

434
00:23:57,435 --> 00:24:01,315
THERE'S NO DOUBT IN MY MIND.

435
00:24:01,357 --> 00:24:02,440
ARCHER: BY THE AIR DUCT.

436
00:24:02,482 --> 00:24:04,068
DO YOU SEE IT?

437
00:24:04,110 --> 00:24:06,028
PHLOX: THAT'S JUST
THE FILTER BRACKET.

438
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:09,073
FOR THE PAST FEW MONTHS,
I'VE NOTICED INCREASING FRICTION

439
00:24:09,115 --> 00:24:11,449
BETWEEN YOU
AND THE SUBCOMMANDER.

440
00:24:11,491 --> 00:24:13,077
YOU MUST UNDERSTAND
THAT I'M TRAINED

441
00:24:13,119 --> 00:24:14,452
TO OBSERVE THESE THINGS.

442
00:24:14,494 --> 00:24:17,248
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT
TO YOUR TRAINING,

443
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:18,999
YOU'RE WRONG.

444
00:24:19,041 --> 00:24:20,751
T'POL AND I HAVE BEEN
GETTING ALONG JUST FINE.

445
00:24:20,793 --> 00:24:22,378
SO LET IT ALONE.

446
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:25,463
PHLOX: WHEN ONE PERSON BELIEVES
THEIR SEXUAL ATTRACTION

447
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:26,882
TOWARD ANOTHER IS INAPPROPRIATE,

448
00:24:26,924 --> 00:24:28,968
THEY OFTEN EXHIBIT
UNEXPECTED BEHAVIOR...

449
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:32,179
SUCH AS INORDINATE ANGER
TOWARD COMPARISONS

450
00:24:32,221 --> 00:24:35,975
MADE BETWEEN THEIR SHIP
AND THEIR BEAGLE. [ CHUCKLES ]

451
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:38,476
[ SIGHS ]
LISTEN, DOC --

452
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:39,937
[ SQUEAKS ]

453
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:41,605
THERE'S NO SEXUAL ATTRACTION.

454
00:24:41,647 --> 00:24:43,357
PHLOX: SHE'S COMING BACK DOWN!

455
00:24:43,399 --> 00:24:45,901
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

456
00:24:45,943 --> 00:24:47,778
WATCH OUT!
WATCH OUT!

457
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:49,322
DON'T LET HER IN THE CORRIDOR!

458
00:24:49,363 --> 00:24:50,448
HEY, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

459
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:52,490
WHAT ARE THEY TRYING
TO DO TO YOU?

460
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:54,076
[ SIGHS ]

461
00:24:57,663 --> 00:25:00,498
THE KREETASSANS CALLED, SIR.

462
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:02,126
ARCHER: WHAT FOR?

463
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:04,086
THEY'RE ANXIOUS
TO GET YOUR RESPONSE

464
00:25:04,128 --> 00:25:05,629
TO THEIR LAST TRANSMISSION.

465
00:25:05,671 --> 00:25:08,506
IT'S THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.

466
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:10,134
